System Design Document

## System Scope ##

### In Scope ###

- Static single-page website.
- Anchored navigation between page sections.
- Responsive desktop and mobile layout.
- Mobile navigation menu.
- Dark blue visual theme.
- Lightweight JavaScript interactions.
- Profile content rendered directly in HTML or JavaScript data objects.
- Optional handling for CV, LinkedIn, email, and profile image.

### Out Of Scope ###

- Backend API.
- Database.
- Login or user account.
- Admin content management.
- Form submission backend.
- Frameworks such as React, Vue, Angular, Next.js, Bootstrap, or Tailwind.
- Analytics or user tracking.

### System Components ###

| Component | Type | Responsibility |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `index.html` | HTML | Defines page structure, semantic sections, content placeholders, and navigation. |
| `styles.css` | CSS | Defines dark blue theme, layout, responsive behavior, cards, timeline, and animations. |
| `script.js` | JavaScript | Handles mobile menu, smooth navigation behavior, active nav state, reveal effects, and optional content visibility. |
| Profile Content | Static Content | Stores profile text, timeline entries, job details, domain exposure, credentials, education, and contact details. |
| Optional Assets | Static Assets | Stores profile photo or CV file if provided. |

### File Structure ###

```text
/
|-- index.html
|-- styles.css
|-- script.js
|-- assets/
    |-- profile.jpg
    |-- resume.pdf
```

`assets/` is optional and should be created only if profile image or CV assets are available.

### Responsive Rules ###

- Desktop: two-column hero layout, grid cards, vertical timeline.
- Mobile: single-column layout, stacked cards, mobile menu.

### Business Impact ###

- Improves personal branding and professional communication.
- Gives recruiters and hiring managers a structured view of experience.
- Supports clearer storytelling around QA, system analysis, and delivery capability.
